# Copy to `.env` in this directory for local development.
# In production, set the same variables in your host (e.g. Netlify) — no `.env` file required.
#
# Product URLs must be absolute http(s), e.g. http://localhost:5174 — no quotes needed.
# After editing `.env`, restart `npm run dev` so Vite picks up changes.
#
# Dev server ports are fixed in each app’s vite.config.ts (not here):
#   Marketing   http://localhost:5173   npm run dev
#   EventHub    http://localhost:5174   npm run dev:eventhub
#   Mesh        http://localhost:5175   npm run dev:mesh
#   Pointy      http://localhost:5176   npm run dev:pointy

# --- Marketing site (repository root) ---
# When set to absolute http(s) URLs, product routes redirect out to these deploys.
# VITE_EVENTHUB_URL=https://eventhub.example.com
# VITE_MESH_URL=https://mesh.example.com
# VITE_POINTY_URL=https://pointy.example.com
# VITE_CHANGELOG_URL=https://volnux.netlify.app/products/changelog

# --- EventHub, Mesh, and Pointy apps ---
# Base URL of the marketing site (Mesh/Pointy chrome; EventHub Docs/Mesh links when unset → root-relative paths).
# For local dev with EventHub on :5174 and marketing on :5173, uncomment:
# VITE_MARKETING_URL=http://localhost:5173
